---
description: Data integrity rules for STFC constants and structured game data
globs: data/**/*
alwaysApply: false
---
The data folder is a source of truth for game constants and structured game data.

Rules:
- Always reference the data/ folder for game constants, ship stats, officer data, and combat parameters.
- Do not silently invent missing constants.
- Keep source values distinct from derived values.
- Preserve the distinction between raw imported data, normalized values, and final derived simulator values.
- If a constant is missing or uncertain, document the gap instead of guessing.
